id: pm-1nht
title: "pm validate: ok:false on warn-only checks + dumps every item ID per field"
description: "Dogfood 2026-05-22 HIGH (agent UX + token): on a healthy project, validate returns ok:false purely because warn-level checks fire (closed missing resolution, missing acceptance_criteria/etc under core profile), and lists every affected ID for every field (NxM payload). Agents read ok:false as a hard failure and may abort; the ID lists are very token-heavy. Fix: top-level ok=true when only warn checks fire (separate ok from has_warnings); aggregate/truncate per-field ID lists by default with counts, full lists behind --verbose. Keep the remediation hints."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-05-22T15:44:32.363Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T09:22:23.145Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Resolution metadata backfilled during active tracker hygiene; existing closure comments and history remain the detailed source of truth.
expected_result: "Closed item has explicit resolution, expected_result, and actual_result metadata so pm validate can confirm closure hygiene."
actual_result: Metadata fields backfilled without changing the closed status or implementation history.
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-22T19:21:10.496Z",codex-validate-worker-20260522,"Implementation plan: separate hard validation failures from warning-only checks so top-level ok stays true for warnings; keep warnings visible via has_warnings/warnings; compact metadata and resolution ID arrays by default while preserving counts and truncation markers; add focused validate regression coverage and run an isolated temp-project validate smoke."
  "2026-05-22T19:25:17.430Z",codex-validate-worker-20260522,"Evidence: focused regression passed: PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/validate-command.spec.ts tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts (57 tests). Manual isolated temp-project smoke passed using node dist/cli.js: validate --check-resolution now returns ok=true and has_warnings=true for warning-only missing resolution; validate --check-resolution --strict-exit still exits non-zero as expected."
  "2026-05-22T19:36:30.855Z",codex-validate-worker-20260522,"Evidence update: first full release gate exposed two stale integration expectations for validate warning-only ok semantics. Updated tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts to assert ok=true plus has_warnings=true while strict-exit/fail-on-warn still exit 1. Focused integration rerun passed: PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts -t 'supports close validation modes and standalone validate command|records telemetry classifications for strict-exit runtime and parse failures' (2 passed, 71 skipped)."
